fields.name: Use_this_section_to_describe_the_request_An_applicant_seeking_a_variance_has_the
fields.fieldText: Use this section to describe the request. An applicant seeking a variance has the burden of presenting evidence sufficient to allow the Board of Adjustment to reach conclusions for the Required Findings of Fact. If you have additional sheets/pertinent information upload them after application submittal as necessary.

fields.name: FindingFacts
fields.fieldText: UDO Section: 2:3:29 Variance requires applications requesting a Variance to address the following findings. The burden of proof is on the applicant and failure to adequately address the findings may result in denial of the application. Please attach additional pages if necessary.

fields.name: Unnecessary_hardship_would_result_from_the_strict_application_of_the_ordinance_I
fields.fieldText: Unnecessary hardship would result from the strict application of the ordinance. It shall not be necessary todemonstrate that, in the absence of the variance, no reasonable use can be made of the property.

fields.name: The_hardship_results_from_conditions_that_are_peculiar_to_the_property_such_as_l
fields.fieldText: ii. The hardship results from conditions that are peculiar to the property, such as location, size, or topography.Hardships resulting from person circumstances, as well as hardships resulting from conditions that are commonto the neighborhood or the general public, may not be the basis for granting a variance.

fields.name: The_hardship_did_not_result_from_actions_taken_by_the_applicant_or_the_proper
fields.fieldText: iii.The hardship did not result from actions taken by the applicant or the property owner. The act of purchasing property with knowledge that circumstances exist that may justify the granting of a variance shall not be regarded as a self-created hardship.

fields.name: The_requested_variance_is_consistent_with_the_spirit_purpose_and_intent_of_th
fields.fieldText: iv.The requested variance is consistent with the spirit, purpose, and intent of the ordinance, such that public safetyis secured, and substantial justice is achieved.

fields.name: The_Variance_approval_is_the_minimum_necessary_to_make_possible_the_reasonable
fields.fieldText: v. The Variance approval is the minimum necessary to make possible the reasonable use of the land, building, or structure.
